Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "povedi" in different forms and positions:

1. Povedi me sa sobom. (*Povedi*, imperative) (Take me with you.)
2. Kada se budeš vraćao, *povedi* i Anju. (*Povedi*, imperative) (When you come back, take Anja with you too.)
3. Neka tvoj brat *povede* prijatelje. (*Povede*, present tense) (Let your brother take his friends with him.)
4. Da li si *poveo* sve što ti je trebalo? (*Poveo*, past tense) (Did you take everything you needed?)
5. Juče sam *povela* decu u park. (*Povela*, past tense) (Yesterday I took the kids to the park.)
6. Ona će *povesti* svoje prijatelje na izlet. (*Povesti*, future tense) (She will take her friends on a trip.)
7. Želela bih da me *povedeš* na večeru. (*Povedeš*, subjunctive) (I would like you to take me out to dinner.)
8. Kada bih imala novca, *povela* bih te na putovanje. (*Povela*, conditional) (If I had the money, I would take you on a trip.)

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.